n===Kiddieland===\n* Baby Barons\n* Merry-Go-Round\n* Frog Hopper\n* Kiddie Autos\n* Kiddie Boats\n* Kiddie Fire Trucks\n* Kiddie Whips\n* Mini Pirate Ship\n* Winky the Whale\n* Pumpkin Ferris Wheel (removed)\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_rides_children|title=Children Rides|last=|first=|date=|publisher=Morgan RV resorts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806051454/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_rides_children|archive-date=August 6, 2011|accessdate=June 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Ideal Beach Water Park===\n* 5 Tube Slides (3 Enclosed)\n* Action River&nbsp;\u2013 [[Lazy river]]\n* Big Flush [[Water Coaster (roller coaster)|Water Coaster]]\n* Sandy Beach Swimming Area with recirculating pool\n* Splash Bash Water Spray Pad<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_waterpark|title=Indiana Beach Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|publisher=Morgan RV resorts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713025602/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_waterpark|archive-date=July 13, 2011|accessdate=June 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Attractions==\n\n===Attractions===\n* Cap'n Crow's Bumper Boats\n* Dr. Frankenstein's Haunted Castle&nbsp;\u2013 A walk-through attraction\n* [[SkyCoaster]]\n\n===Former attractions===\n* Adventure Point\n* Boat Tag\n\n==Games==\n* [[Fascination (game)|Fascination]]\n* Gallery of Ghouls&nbsp;\u2013 [[wikt:shooting gallery|Shooting gallery]]\n* [[Skee Ball]]\n* Video Arcade\n* 21\n* Quackerz<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_games|title=Indiana Beach Games|last=|first=|date=|work=Indiana Beach|publisher=Morgan RV resorts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713025325/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_games|archive-date=July 13, 2011|accessdate=June 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Lodging and cabins==\nLodging at Indiana Beach includes hotel, motel and cabin accommodations with varying prices, sleeping capacities and amenities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/ATIndianaBeachAccommodations|title=Indiana Beach Amusement Resort: Amusement Park, Hotel, Campground & Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|website=Indiana Beach|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414080647/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/ATIndianaBeachAccommodations|archive-date=April 14, 2013|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>  There are also campground facilities named Indiana Beach/Monticello KOA containing approximately 1,000 camp sites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/rensselaer_republican/news/local/indiana-beach-unveils-new-campground-name/article_06e84b08-cc6f-519f-ac7c-af1b52b74411.html|title=Indiana Beach unveils new campground name|last=Johnson|first=Michael|date=May 17, 2019|website=Newsbug|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/AtOurCampgrounds|title=Indiana Beach Amusement Resort: Amusement Park, Hotel, Campground & Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|website=Indiana Beach|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414075438/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/AtOurCampgrounds|archive-date=April 14, 2013|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nIn 2011, former and current employees staged a protest due to working and safety conditions at the park, claiming that \"Rides are continuously closed, or many times forced to be open using rigged components because the company will not or cannot pay for the parts that will allow maintenance to fix them properly.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screamscape.com/html/indiana_beach.htm|title=Indiana Beach|last=|first=|date=January 16, 2012|website=Screamscape|accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/Former-workers-protest-Indiana-Beach|title=Former workers protest Indiana Beach|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[WLFI]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025023106/http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/Former-workers-protest-Indiana-Beach|archive-date=2011-10-25|accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref>  An inspector from the state's division of [[Homeland Security]] investigated as a result of the protest and found no major safety violations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newsbug.info/articles/2011/09/01/monticello_herald_journal/local_news/doc4e5819a381a4f497271293.txt|title=Inspector: IB rides safe|last=Allen|first=Scott|date=August 28, 2011|website=Herald Journal|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIt was reported in December 2012 that Morgan RV LLC had sold 11 of its properties to Sun Communities Operating Limited Partnership LLC of Michigan for $135 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rvbusiness.com/2012/12/sun-communities-buys-11-morgan-rv-resorts|title=Sun Communities Buys 11 Morgan RV Resorts|last=|first=|date=December 18, 2012|website=|publisher=RV Business|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320123131/http://www.rvbusiness.com/2012/12/sun-communities-buys-11-morgan-rv-resorts/|archive-date=2016-03-20|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>  Among the listed properties was Ideal Private Resorts LLC, whose website includes Indiana Beach Amusement Park and Indiana Beach Accommodations as destinations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://idealprivateresorts.com/public/?page_id=64|title=Destinations &#124; IPR Main|last=|first=|date=|website=Ideal Private Resorts|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref> Calls by news media to Morgan RV LLC requesting comment, including confirmation or denial that all or part of Indiana Beach was included in the sale, went unanswered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://posttrib.suntimes.com/news/17710233-418/county-indiana-beach-owes-347000-in-taxes.html|title=White County: Indiana Beach owes $347,000 in taxes - Post-Tribune|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=PostTrib SunTimes|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728214219/http://posttrib.suntimes.com/news/17710233-418/county-indiana-beach-owes-347000-in-taxes.html|archive-date=July 28, 2014|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2013, local news affiliates reported Morgan RV LLC was delinquent paying property and innkeeper taxes totaling approximately $347,000 to White County, where Indiana Beach is located.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/monticello_herald_journal/news/local/article_67e35296-5ec5-11e2-bd44-001a4bcf887a.html|title=Despite payment, Beach owes $347k|last=Rodenberger|first=Gwen|date=January 14, 2013|website=Newsbug|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wthr.com/story/20637443/county-officials-indiana-beach-owes-347000|title=County officials: Indiana Beach owes $347,000|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=|publisher=[[WTHR]]|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.woodallscm.com/2013/01/morgan-rv-resorts-park-faces-347k-tax-bill/|title=Morgan RV Resorts Park Faces $347K Tax Bill &#124; Woodall's Campground Management|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=Woodallscm|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124020204/http://www.woodallscm.com/2013/01/morgan-rv-resorts-park-faces-347k-tax-bill/|archive-date=2013-01-24|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/monticello_herald_journal/news/local/article_3dcff216-903e-11e2-b86c-0019bb2963f4.html|title=Indiana Beach: Innkeepers taxes paid|last=Rodenberger|first=Gwen|date=March 18, 2013|website=Newsbug|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/indiana-beach-all-clear-on-its-taxes|title=Indiana Beach all clear on its taxes|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[WLFI]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130412043202/http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/indiana-beach-all-clear-on-its-taxes|archive-date=2013-04-12|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref> The CEO of then-owner Morgan RV, Robert Moser, and Indiana Beach's general manager, Bob Gallagher, stated that the park would open for the 2014 season despite misgivings stated by Monticello residents and business owners.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2019, a twelve-year-old boy died after suffering a medical emergency on a roller coaster at the park; it was determined it was not caused by Indiana Beach or the ride.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jconline.com/story/news/local/lafayette/2019/06/28/lafayette-boy-dies-after-medical-emergency-indiana-beach/1596955001/|title=Lafayette boy dies after medical emergency at Indiana Beach|last=Wilkins|first=Ron|date=June 28, 2019|website=Journal & Courier|access-date=September 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n {{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.indianabeach.com/ Indiana Beach Amusement Resort]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081204024930/http://www.coasterimage.com/pictures/indiana-beach-pictures/ Photos of Indiana Beach]\n*{{RCDB|4599}}\n\n{{Indiana Beach Coasters |state=expanded}}\n{{Amusement parks in Indiana}}\n[[Category:Defunct amusement parks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Amusement parks in Indiana]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in Indiana]]\n[[Category:2020 disestablishments in Indiana]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in White County, Indiana]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in White County, Indiana]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American amusement park}}\n{{For|the unincorporated community where the park is located|Indiana Beach, Indiana}}{{Infobox amusement park\n| name = Indiana Beach\n| logo = IndianaBeach logo.png\n| logo_size = 300px\n| caption = \n| location = [[Monticello, Indiana|Monticello]], [[White County, Indiana|White County]]\n| location2 = Indiana\n| location3 = United States\n| coordinates = {{coord|40.79|N|86.77|W|display=inline,title}}\n| owner = [[Apex Parks Group]]\n| opening_date = 1926\n| season = May through October\n| rides = 43\n| coasters = 5\n| area_ acre = 10\n| address = 5224 East Indiana Beach Blvd <br /> Monticello, Indiana 47960\n| previous_name(s) = Ideal Beach; Indiana Beach Amusement Resort\n| water_slides = 4\n| slogan = ''\"Where Families Flock For Fun\"'' (previously: ''\"There's more than corn in Indiana!\"'' & ''\"The riviera of the midwest!\"'')\n| homepage = http://www.indianabeach.com\n| status = Open\n}}\n\n'''Indiana Beach''' is an amusement park located on [[Lake Shafer]] in [[Monticello, Indiana]]. The resort was developed by the Spackman family, who owned it from 1926 to 2008. The park was then sold to Morgan RV LLC, who sold it to Apex Parks Group in 2015. Apex announced Indiana Beach's closure in February 2020. Following Apex Parks' bankruptcy in April 2020, the park's social media began teasing a possible reopening, with an announcement on April 23rd that the park would be open for the 2020 season.\n\n== History ==\nOriginally named Ideal Beach, the [[amusement park]] began as a small lakeside beach with a bath house and refreshment stand. In 1927, the first thrill attraction opened, and from that point, it began to expand.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/life/2016/07/04/indiana-beach-new-beginning/86153880/|title=For Indiana Beach, a new beginning|last=Grady|first=Danielle|date=July 4, 2016|website=IndyStar|access-date=}}</ref> In the 1930s and 1940s, it was popular for the Ideal Beach Ballroom, featuring well-known bands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_history#|title=Indiana Beach Amusement Resort: History|last=|first=|date=|website=Indiana Beach|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101012642/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_history|archive-date=November 1, 2013|accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref> In February 2008, it was announced that both the amusement park and Indiana Beach campgrounds had been sold to Morgan RV LLC.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/entertainment/2013/12/29/worries-grow-about-indiana-beach-future/4244841/|title=Worries grow about Indiana Beach future|last=Livingston|first=Mikel|date=December 29, 2013|website=IndyStar|access-date=}}</ref> On September 1, 2015, it was announced that the park had been sold to Apex Parks Group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/2016/03/06/indiana-beachs-new-owner-overhauling-amusement-park/81418512/|title=Indiana Beach\u2019s new owner overhauling amusement park|last=AP|first=|date=March 6, 2016|website=IndyStar|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.screamscape.com/html/indiana_beach.htm|title=Indiana Beach|last=|first=|date=|website=www.screamscape.com|access-date=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 18, 2020, Indiana Beach announced that it would permanently close after 94 years of operation, with no plans to reopen. Apex Parks Group cited financial reasons for the closure and said they had \u201cworked diligently\u201d to find a new buyer for the park but were not successful.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wlfi.com/content/news/Indiana-Beach-closes-gates-567980101.html|title=Indiana Beach Closes After Nearly a Century|last=AP|first=|date=February 18, 2020|website=[[WLFI]]|access-date=February 18, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> In addition to dozens of seasonal workers, Indiana Beach employed 27 people in administrative and maintenance positions. Those workers were offered six weeks compensation.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wthr.com/article/indiana-beach-close-after-94-years|title=Indiana Beach to Close after 94 Years|last=AP|first=|date=February 18, 2020|website=[[WTHR]]|access-date=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Apex Parks Group said that it was in discussions with potential buyers of the park, and that it was possible that the park would be able to reopen this year. Because Indiana Beach generates a large part of the county's tourism revenue, [[White County, Indiana|White County]] officials have agreed to offer $3 million from the White County Windfarm Economic Development Fund to the buyer after the sale is complete.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.ibj.com/articles/owner-indiana-beach-amusement-park-could-reopen-this-year|title=Owner: Indiana Beach amusement park could reopen this year|date=March 22, 2020|work=[[Indianapolis Business Journal]]|access-date=March 23, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, Indiana Beach announced that the park would be reopening that year. Little details are known yet including the purchaser of the park.\n\n==Rides==\n[[Image:IBeach ShaferQueen DSCN9212.JPG|right|thumb|250px|Shafer Queen]]\n[[Image:IBeach HurricaneDrop DSCN9199.JPG|right|thumb|250px|Hoosier Hurricane]]\n[[Image:Flyers-IndianaBeach.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Air Crow]]\n[[Image:IB-fascination.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Carnival Games]]\n\n===Roller coasters===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Type !! Design !! Year Opened !! Year Closed !! Manufacturer\n|-\n| [[Cornball Express]] || Wood || Twister || 2001 ||  ||[[Custom Coasters International|CCI]]\n|-\n| [[Hoosier Hurricane]] || Wood || Out and Back || 1994 ||  ||[[Custom Coasters International|CCI]]\n|-\n| [[Lost Coaster of Superstition Mountain]] || Wood || Elevator Lift || 2002 ||  ||[[Custom Coasters International|CCI]]\n|-\n| [[Steel Hawg]] || Steel || [[El Loco (roller coaster)|El Loco]] || 2008 ||  || S&S\n|-\n| [[Tig'rr Coaster]] || Steel || Jet Star || 1984 ||  ||[[Schwarzkopf]]\n|-\n| [[Dragon Wagon (Indiana Beach)|Dragon Wagon]] || Steel || Kiddie || 2014 || 2018 || Wisdom Rides\n|-\n| [[Galaxi]] || Steel || [[Galaxi]] || 1971 || 2013 || S.D.C.\n|}\n<ref name=\"Indiana Beach RCDB\">{{cite RCDB|coaster_name=Indiana Beach|location=|rcdb_number=4599|metric=|accessdate=June 25, 2019|url=}}</ref>\n\n===Major rides===\n* Air Crow&nbsp;\u2013 [[Flying Scooters]]\n* Antique Autos\n* Den of Lost Thieves&nbsp;\u2013 Shooting [[dark ride]]\n* Dodgem&nbsp;\u2013 [[Bumper cars]]\n* Double Shot&nbsp;\u2013 [[S&S Power]] [[Double Shot (ride)|Double Shot]] tower ride\n* 