ash Water Spray Pad<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_waterpark|title=Indiana Beach Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|publisher=Morgan RV resorts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713025602/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_waterpark|archive-date=July 13, 2011|accessdate=June 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Attractions==\n\n===Attractions===\n* Cap'n Crow's Bumper Boats\n* Dr. Frankenstein's Haunted Castle&nbsp;\u2013 A walk-through attraction\n* [[SkyCoaster]]\n\n===Former attractions===\n* Adventure Point\n* Boat Tag\n\n==Games==\n* [[Fascination (game)|Fascination]]\n* Gallery of Ghouls&nbsp;\u2013 [[wikt:shooting gallery|Shooting gallery]]\n* [[Skee Ball]]\n* Video Arcade\n* 21\n* Quackerz<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_games|title=Indiana Beach Games|last=|first=|date=|work=Indiana Beach|publisher=Morgan RV resorts|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713025325/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/indianabeach_games|archive-date=July 13, 2011|accessdate=June 17, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Lodging and cabins==\nLodging at Indiana Beach includes hotel, motel and cabin accommodations with varying prices, sleeping capacities and amenities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/ATIndianaBeachAccommodations|title=Indiana Beach Amusement Resort: Amusement Park, Hotel, Campground & Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|website=Indiana Beach|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414080647/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/ATIndianaBeachAccommodations|archive-date=April 14, 2013|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>  There are also campground facilities named Indiana Beach/Monticello KOA containing approximately 1,000 camp sites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/rensselaer_republican/news/local/indiana-beach-unveils-new-campground-name/article_06e84b08-cc6f-519f-ac7c-af1b52b74411.html|title=Indiana Beach unveils new campground name|last=Johnson|first=Michael|date=May 17, 2019|website=Newsbug|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/AtOurCampgrounds|title=Indiana Beach Amusement Resort: Amusement Park, Hotel, Campground & Waterpark|last=|first=|date=|website=Indiana Beach|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414075438/http://www.indianabeach.com/pages/AtOurCampgrounds|archive-date=April 14, 2013|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nIn 2011, former and current employees staged a protest due to working and safety conditions at the park, claiming that \"Rides are continuously closed, or many times forced to be open using rigged components because the company will not or cannot pay for the parts that will allow maintenance to fix them properly.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screamscape.com/html/indiana_beach.htm|title=Indiana Beach|last=|first=|date=January 16, 2012|website=Screamscape|accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/Former-workers-protest-Indiana-Beach|title=Former workers protest Indiana Beach|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[WLFI]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025023106/http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/Former-workers-protest-Indiana-Beach|archive-date=2011-10-25|accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref>  An inspector from the state's division of [[Homeland Security]] investigated as a result of the protest and found no major safety violations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newsbug.info/articles/2011/09/01/monticello_herald_journal/local_news/doc4e5819a381a4f497271293.txt|title=Inspector: IB rides safe|last=Allen|first=Scott|date=August 28, 2011|website=Herald Journal|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIt was reported in December 2012 that Morgan RV LLC had sold 11 of its properties to Sun Communities Operating Limited Partnership LLC of Michigan for $135 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rvbusiness.com/2012/12/sun-communities-buys-11-morgan-rv-resorts|title=Sun Communities Buys 11 Morgan RV Resorts|last=|first=|date=December 18, 2012|website=|publisher=RV Business|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320123131/http://www.rvbusiness.com/2012/12/sun-communities-buys-11-morgan-rv-resorts/|archive-date=2016-03-20|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>  Among the listed properties was Ideal Private Resorts LLC, whose website includes Indiana Beach Amusement Park and Indiana Beach Accommodations as destinations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://idealprivateresorts.com/public/?page_id=64|title=Destinations &#124; IPR Main|last=|first=|date=|website=Ideal Private Resorts|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref> Calls by news media to Morgan RV LLC requesting comment, including confirmation or denial that all or part of Indiana Beach was included in the sale, went unanswered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://posttrib.suntimes.com/news/17710233-418/county-indiana-beach-owes-347000-in-taxes.html|title=White County: Indiana Beach owes $347,000 in taxes - Post-Tribune|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=PostTrib SunTimes|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728214219/http://posttrib.suntimes.com/news/17710233-418/county-indiana-beach-owes-347000-in-taxes.html|archive-date=July 28, 2014|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2013, local news affiliates reported Morgan RV LLC was delinquent paying property and innkeeper taxes totaling approximately $347,000 to White County, where Indiana Beach is located.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/monticello_herald_journal/news/local/article_67e35296-5ec5-11e2-bd44-001a4bcf887a.html|title=Despite payment, Beach owes $347k|last=Rodenberger|first=Gwen|date=January 14, 2013|website=Newsbug|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wthr.com/story/20637443/county-officials-indiana-beach-owes-347000|title=County officials: Indiana Beach owes $347,000|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=|publisher=[[WTHR]]|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.woodallscm.com/2013/01/morgan-rv-resorts-park-faces-347k-tax-bill/|title=Morgan RV Resorts Park Faces $347K Tax Bill &#124; Woodall's Campground Management|last=|first=|date=January 21, 2013|website=Woodallscm|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124020204/http://www.woodallscm.com/2013/01/morgan-rv-resorts-park-faces-347k-tax-bill/|archive-date=2013-01-24|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsbug.info/monticello_herald_journal/news/local/article_3dcff216-903e-11e2-b86c-0019bb2963f4.html|title=Indiana Beach: Innkeepers taxes paid|last=Rodenberger|first=Gwen|date=March 18, 2013|website=Newsbug|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/indiana-beach-all-clear-on-its-taxes|title=Indiana Beach all clear on its taxes|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[WLFI]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130412043202/http://www.wlfi.com/dpp/news/local/indiana-beach-all-clear-on-its-taxes|archive-date=2013-04-12|accessdate=April 20, 2013}}</ref> The CEO of then-owner Morgan RV, Robert Moser, and Indiana Beach's general manager, Bob Gallagher, stated that the park would open for the 2014 season despite misgivings stated by Monticello residents and business owners.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2019, a twelve-year-old boy died after suffering a medical emergency on a roller coaster at the park; it was determined it was not caused by Indiana Beach or the ride.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jconline.com/story/news/local/lafayette/2019/06/28/lafayette-boy-dies-after-medical-emergency-indiana-beach/1596955001/|title=Lafayette boy dies after medical emergency at Indiana Beach|last=Wilkins|first=Ron|date=June 28, 2019|website=Journal & Courier|access-date=September 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n {{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.indianabeach.com/ Indiana Beach Amusement Resort